==English==
{{wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
A part-translation of Old French ''[[nois mugede]]'' (modern ''[[noix muscade]]''), from mediaeval Latin ''[[nux muscata]]'', literally ‘musky nut’.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈnʌtmɛg/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# an [[evergreen]] [[tree]], ''[[Myristica fragrans]]'', cultivated in the [[East Indies]] for its [[spicy]] [[seed]]s
# the [[aromatic]] seed of this tree, used as a [[spice]]
# a [[grey]]-[[brown]] [[colour]]
# {{soccer}} The [[playing]] of the [[ball]] between the [[leg]]s of an [[opponent]]

